# Contributor Code of Conduct

## Our Pledge

In the interest of fostering an open and welcoming environment, we as contributors and maintainers pledge to make participation in this project a harassment-free experience for everyone.

## Our Standards

Examples of behavior that contributes to a positive environment include:

* Showing respect and understanding for differing viewpoints and experiences.
* Graceful, constructive communication and feedback.
* Focusing on whatâ€™s best for the community and the project.

Examples of unacceptable behavior:

* Harassment, discrimination, or insulting/derogatory comments.
* Posting private information (doxing).
* Sustained disruption of project discussions.

## Enforcement

Project maintainers may remove, edit, or reject contributions or ban participants at their discretion if they believe someone has violated the Code of Conduct.

## Reporting

If you are being harassed or notice a violation, please contact the maintainers at: `nouridinelhofy@gmail.com`. In urgent cases, include subject line: `[Code of Conduct]` and as much context as possible.

## Attribution

This Code of Conduct is adapted from the Contributor Covenant, version 2.1.
